{"cursor":"8324","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Proposed deletion/dated |concern = This page appears to be a vanity article,\nwritten to publicize the fringe theories of Joseph Jordania. The term \"battle\ntrance\" does not exist outside of Jordania's own writings and the phenomenon it\ndescribes is not supported by other sources. (The other sources cited in this\narticle do not mention battle trance or any other similar phenomena but instead\ntalk about well known military- and war-related topics.) |timestamp =\n20130812192718 }}\n\n'Battle trance' is a term denoting a specific altered state of consciousness\nthat characterizes the psychological state of combatants during a combat\nsituation. In this state, combatants do not feel fear or pain (analgesia), and\nall the individual members of group (unit) are acting as one collective\norganism. In this state, combatants' individuality is suppressed or displaced\nentirely, being replaced partially or entirely by collective identity; as a\nresult, combatants become predisposed to unquestioning obedience of orders, in\nthe process losing their capacity for independent rational deliberation and\nevaluation of their conduct. In a battle trance, any given human may behave very\ndifferently than he or she normally does, to the point of extreme altruism\n(usually directed toward members of one's \"in-group,\" e.g., sacrifice of one's\nlife to protect other soldiers on one's side of the conflict) and/or extreme\naggression (usually directed toward members of an \"out-group\" opposed or\nperceived as opposed to the combatant's group, e.g., massacres or mass murders\nof prisoners of war, noncombatant military personnel protected by treaty, and/or\ncivilian inhabitants of foreign or foreign-occupied territory). As Jesse\nGlenn Gray puts it in his 1959 book \"The warriors: reflection on men in battle\":\n\"War reveals dimensions of human nature both above and below the acceptable\nstandards for humanity.\" Battle trance affects both men and women and can\nbe induced in individuals as well as groups. Battle trance state may occur\ninvoluntarily (for example, mother acting in total disregard of her own safety\nwhen her child is suddenly attacked), or can be induced by ritualistic behavior,\ninvolving loud rhythmic group singing, stomping and drumming on external\nsubjects, as well as the use of different substances.\n","linknr":205,"url":"Battle_trance","recorded":1376422799,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Battle_trance&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Battle_trance&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_trance","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.visualEditor.viewPageTarget.noscript&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Wikipedia:Proposed_deletion","/wiki/Joseph_Jordania","/wiki/Wikipedia:Editing_policy","/wiki/Wikipedia:Manual_of_Style","/wiki/Help:Introduction_to_referencing/1","/wiki/Wikipedia:Renaming_a_page","/wiki/Wikipedia:Merging","//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Battle_trance&action=edit","/wiki/Wikipedia:Deletion_policy","/wiki/Joseph_Jordania","/wiki/Template:Proposed_deletion_notify","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia